The clockevent layer now handles everything done by the ARM 
timer_tick() call, except the LED stuff.  Here we add an
arch_tick_leds() to handle LED toggling which is called by 
do_timer().

Signed-off-by: Kevin Hilman <khilman@mvista.com>
---
 arch/arm/kernel/time.c |    7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

Index: linux-2.6.25.4-rt1/arch/arm/kernel/time.c
===================================================================
--- linux-2.6.25.4-rt1.orig/arch/arm/kernel/time.c	2008-05-17 08:26:43.000000000 -0400
+++ linux-2.6.25.4-rt1/arch/arm/kernel/time.c	2008-05-17 08:26:59.000000000 -0400
@@ -225,6 +225,13 @@ static inline void do_leds(void)
 #define	do_leds()
 #endif
 
+void arch_tick_leds(void)
+{
+#ifdef CONFIG_LEDS_TIMER
+	do_leds();
+#endif
+}
